WEBVTT

00:07.268 --> 00:08.530
- Previously on
"The Magicians"...

00:08.573 --> 00:09.835
- Will you play with me?
- No!

00:09.879 --> 00:11.359
- You do remember me,
don't you?

00:11.402 --> 00:12.795
I--I'm Christopher--
- Plover.

00:12.838 --> 00:14.797
- You were looking
for your book.

00:14.840 --> 00:17.756
Yours and your friends' books
are in the Revision Room.

00:17.800 --> 00:19.584
But I happen to know
where that is.

00:19.628 --> 00:22.457
- The end of Quentin's book.
He's going to die.

00:22.500 --> 00:24.372
- Isn't that how all books end?

00:24.415 --> 00:25.721
- His ends next week.

00:25.764 --> 00:27.375
- Your birthright box,

00:27.418 --> 00:29.812
which it has been
my honor to guard,

00:29.855 --> 00:32.597
dictated your absence
from the kingdom

00:32.641 --> 00:33.859
and your return.

00:33.903 --> 00:36.819
- We need your help, Shoshana.

00:36.862 --> 00:38.647
- I have a new deity to follow.

00:38.690 --> 00:40.257
- The Poison Room fountain

00:40.301 --> 00:42.390
has a stack of books
for a statue.

00:42.433 --> 00:43.521
- So if we find
the right fountain...

00:43.565 --> 00:44.522
- We can walk right in.

00:44.566 --> 00:45.654
- When you get back

00:45.697 --> 00:47.264
what the gods took from you,

00:47.308 --> 00:50.398
could I maybe
have Eliot back?

00:50.441 --> 00:52.878
- You were friends
with Eliot.

00:52.922 --> 00:54.924
The very best of friends.

00:54.967 --> 00:58.754
You should know that
your friend Eliot is dead.

00:58.797 --> 01:01.670
I felt the moment
his soul died.

01:01.713 --> 01:03.454
- Or he's trapped in there.

01:03.498 --> 01:05.282
Forced to watch everything
the Monster does,

01:05.326 --> 01:09.156
just waiting for us
to find a way to help him.

01:10.896 --> 01:13.595
- [shouting]
Hello?

01:16.163 --> 01:17.599
There's one thing

01:17.642 --> 01:19.905
every resident
of the Physical Kids cottage

01:19.949 --> 01:20.906
must know.

01:20.950 --> 01:22.517
- Where the bathroom is.

01:22.560 --> 01:23.518
- How to make...

01:23.561 --> 01:24.867
- How to make.

01:24.910 --> 01:26.390
- Our signature cocktail.
- How to make

01:26.434 --> 01:27.435
our signature cocktail.

01:27.478 --> 01:28.740
That's what I was trying to--

01:28.784 --> 01:29.915
that's what I meant to say.

01:29.959 --> 01:31.613
[clears throat]

01:31.656 --> 01:32.875
Oh.

01:32.918 --> 01:34.877
- Now you can make it
on your own.

01:34.920 --> 01:37.967
[knocking at door]

01:38.010 --> 01:39.925
- Should I get that?

01:39.969 --> 01:43.277
[knocking at door]

01:43.320 --> 01:46.149
- Rather not.

01:47.890 --> 01:50.284
- Ah. There you are.

01:50.327 --> 01:51.763
- Here I am.

01:51.807 --> 01:54.244
Sorry, I had to interrupt
an orgy upstairs.

01:54.288 --> 01:55.854
- You broke up the orgy?

01:55.898 --> 01:58.205
- No, I told them
there was a bigger room

01:58.248 --> 01:59.249
two doors down.

01:59.293 --> 02:01.295
- Mmm.

02:01.338 --> 02:02.905
Now...

02:02.948 --> 02:04.602
I don't say this lightly,

02:04.646 --> 02:07.388
but I think this might be
our best party yet.

02:07.431 --> 02:10.956
- And I say this with
the weight of my whole heart.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.567
I concur.

02:12.610 --> 02:14.351
[both laughing]

02:14.395 --> 02:15.396
[knocking at door]

02:15.439 --> 02:16.832
- I'll get it.
- Don't.

02:16.875 --> 02:20.183
Whoever is that desperate
to come in can't be fun.

02:24.535 --> 02:26.320
- Oh.

02:26.363 --> 02:28.496
What do you like most
about summer?

02:28.539 --> 02:30.585
- Hmm...

02:30.628 --> 02:32.021
Nothing.

02:32.064 --> 02:33.805
- You don't like summer?

02:36.721 --> 02:38.506
- No.

02:38.549 --> 02:40.856
Nothing's what I love
about summer.

02:40.899 --> 02:42.510
No class.

02:42.553 --> 02:45.556
No people, just...

02:45.600 --> 02:47.819
beautiful nothing.

02:47.863 --> 02:49.778
[knocking at door]

02:49.821 --> 02:53.260
No...

02:53.303 --> 02:55.000
- Go make me a drink.

02:55.044 --> 02:58.613
- Mm-kay.

03:00.876 --> 03:02.530
I'm Eliot, by the way.

03:02.573 --> 03:04.009
- Uh-oh.

03:04.053 --> 03:06.751
That's--Eliot's my name, too.

03:06.795 --> 03:08.275
- Well, that can't be.

03:08.318 --> 03:09.798
What's your middle name?

03:09.841 --> 03:11.060
- Um...

03:11.103 --> 03:12.061
Todd?

03:12.104 --> 03:14.019
[knocking at door]

03:14.063 --> 03:15.369
Should I get that?

03:15.412 --> 03:16.718
- Never answer a cop knock.

03:16.761 --> 03:18.459
- Oh.

03:22.767 --> 03:24.552
- Beautiful nothing.

03:24.595 --> 03:26.858
Now that's the kind of man
I need.

03:26.902 --> 03:28.599
[knocking at door]

03:28.643 --> 03:30.862
- Don't answer it.
Then we have to talk to them.

03:30.906 --> 03:33.778
- Oh, come on.
I just want to see who it is.

03:36.781 --> 03:39.480
No, you can't come in.

03:39.523 --> 03:42.613
Well, I'm sorry, but that
sounds like a you problem.

03:42.657 --> 03:44.398
[screams]
- [screams] Margo!

03:44.441 --> 03:47.618
Margo!

03:52.144 --> 03:55.409
- [screaming] Eliot!

03:57.454 --> 03:58.760
- [groaning] Inside.

03:58.803 --> 04:00.457
- What?
- Inside, we must go inside--

04:00.501 --> 04:01.719
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, no.
Do we know you?

04:01.763 --> 04:02.720
- They're coming.

04:02.764 --> 04:03.721
Let me inside, please.

04:03.765 --> 04:05.114
I won't harm her.

04:05.157 --> 04:06.811
This is only
for your urgent attention.

04:06.855 --> 04:07.943
- [grunting]

04:07.986 --> 04:09.031
- Yeah, I'm not worried about

04:09.074 --> 04:10.641
you harming her.

04:10.685 --> 04:12.556
- [grunting]

04:12.600 --> 04:13.601
[both grunting]

04:13.644 --> 04:16.908
- [screams]

04:16.952 --> 04:19.824
- But you make a point.
Uh, let's go.

04:19.868 --> 04:22.871
[supernatural shrieking]

04:30.879 --> 04:32.968
- Are you done being sad now?

04:33.011 --> 04:34.143
I need your help.

04:34.186 --> 04:35.884
- No, I'm not.

04:35.927 --> 04:39.540
- Is this about your friend?

04:39.583 --> 04:41.629
Because that's not a problem.

04:41.672 --> 04:43.500
I'm your friend.

04:43.544 --> 04:46.068
He's gone, but I'm here.

04:46.111 --> 04:49.376
Same number of friends.

04:49.419 --> 04:51.116
So.

04:54.946 --> 04:57.645
What is this?

04:57.688 --> 04:59.342
- How am I supposed to know?

04:59.386 --> 05:02.519
- I would like for you
to be helpful, Quentin.

05:02.563 --> 05:05.783
- [sighs]
It's...

05:05.827 --> 05:07.655
really old?

05:07.698 --> 05:09.831
Like beginning
of civilization old.

05:09.874 --> 05:11.093
- And where was that?

05:11.136 --> 05:14.009
- Mesopotamia was the first...

05:14.052 --> 05:15.663
- That's very helpful,
thank you.

05:15.706 --> 05:17.534
I will see you
back at the apartment.

05:21.103 --> 05:24.062
[eerie music]

05:24.106 --> 05:31.026
â™ª

05:31.069 --> 05:34.899
- So...spacious.

05:34.943 --> 05:37.075
Mine wasn't nearly
half this size.

05:37.119 --> 05:40.470
- What's with the...

05:40.514 --> 05:43.212
that out there, is it...

05:43.255 --> 05:46.084
Sorry, I'm at a loss for words,
which is new for me.

05:46.128 --> 05:47.695
- I'm sure you're
quite flummoxed.

05:47.738 --> 05:50.480
Sit, sit, sit, sit, sit,
sit, sit, sit, sit.

05:50.524 --> 05:52.047
Well, the good news:

05:52.090 --> 05:55.093
a monster possessed you
and is inhabiting your body.

05:55.137 --> 05:56.791
- What?
- He normally tears people

05:56.834 --> 05:58.880
to shreds, so believe me,
this is preferable.

05:58.923 --> 06:01.535
And when he possessed you,
he thrust all of you

06:01.578 --> 06:02.971
to this nook of your mind

06:03.014 --> 06:04.494
that holds
all your remembrances.

06:04.538 --> 06:07.410
Everything here is remembrance.

06:07.454 --> 06:08.890
Even your friend here.

06:08.933 --> 06:10.848
Now, do me a favor.

06:10.892 --> 06:13.851
Imagine she's not here.

06:18.943 --> 06:20.075
- What the fuck?

06:20.118 --> 06:21.642
- Oh, tell me.

06:21.685 --> 06:22.947
I've been trying
to understand it.

06:22.991 --> 06:24.427
I just can't figure it out.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.560
What is "fuck"?

06:26.603 --> 06:27.778
- Well...

06:27.822 --> 06:29.737
um, well, it's sort of
like a...

06:29.780 --> 06:31.913
a chameleon of a word.

06:31.956 --> 06:34.219
Wait, um...

06:34.263 --> 06:35.482
Who are you?

06:35.525 --> 06:37.745
- Oh, uh, well,

06:37.788 --> 06:39.050
I'm Charlton.

06:39.094 --> 06:42.924
- Now, I have repressed
many memories,

06:42.967 --> 06:46.188
but I would never forget
somebody named Charlton.

06:46.231 --> 06:47.842
- Thank you.
- Not a compliment.

06:47.885 --> 06:49.191
- I'm not a memory.

06:49.234 --> 06:51.628
I once was possessed
by the Monster too.

06:51.672 --> 06:53.935
I was in my memory for...

06:53.978 --> 06:55.066
it's hard to say.

06:55.110 --> 06:56.241
- That's it.

06:56.285 --> 06:57.721
I'm pretty sure I shot you.

06:57.765 --> 06:59.157
Or your body, at least.

06:59.201 --> 07:00.811
Sorry.

07:00.855 --> 07:02.596
- No bother.

07:02.639 --> 07:04.989
It was the Monster's longer
than it was mine.

07:05.033 --> 07:08.036
And I have quite enjoyed
the change of scenery.

07:08.079 --> 07:10.647
This is what I call
your Happy Place.

07:10.691 --> 07:13.084
All your pleasant remembrances
live here.

07:13.128 --> 07:16.131
It's very easy to get content
and lose track of time.

07:16.174 --> 07:17.306
And reality.

07:17.349 --> 07:19.874
- So you're here
to break me out.

07:19.917 --> 07:22.485
My knight in drab armor.

07:22.529 --> 07:23.791
- No, that would be ridiculous.

07:23.834 --> 07:25.793
We stay here.

07:25.836 --> 07:27.534
- We don't.
I'm taking my body back.

07:27.577 --> 07:29.318
- No, no, no, no, no.

07:29.361 --> 07:31.973
This is the only place
the creatures can't come.

07:32.016 --> 07:34.192
- We can't--oh, right.

07:34.236 --> 07:36.847
The scary shrieky things
that live outside.

07:36.891 --> 07:37.848
What are they?

07:37.892 --> 07:40.155
- The Monster's other hosts.

07:40.198 --> 07:42.026
Inmates from the Castle.

07:42.070 --> 07:44.768
Horrible, wretched mistakes
of the gods,

07:44.812 --> 07:46.117
all of them.

07:46.161 --> 07:48.119
- Yeah, but if--if this
is all my memory,

07:48.163 --> 07:49.686
then they can't really
hurt us, right?

07:49.730 --> 07:51.688
- Would you care to ask
the Knight Ora?

07:51.732 --> 07:53.081
She was here before you.

07:53.124 --> 07:54.691
- I would, actually.
- Well, you can't.

07:54.735 --> 07:57.607
Because she's dead.
Dead fuck.

07:57.651 --> 07:59.000
- That's not quite right.

07:59.043 --> 08:01.698
- And I told her that
when you die here,

08:01.742 --> 08:03.744
you're gone forever,
but she just had to try

08:03.787 --> 08:05.920
and find her door, and pray
imagine what befell her?

08:05.963 --> 08:07.661
Devoured by creatures.

08:07.704 --> 08:09.140
Flesh rent from her bones.

08:09.184 --> 08:10.664
Skin torn from her skull.

08:10.707 --> 08:12.579
She died staring
at her own face

08:12.622 --> 08:15.756
held before her.

08:15.799 --> 08:18.193
- That is awful.
- Yeah.

08:18.236 --> 08:19.934
- What's this about a door?

08:19.977 --> 08:22.980
- [whistling]

08:25.243 --> 08:27.115
- Could you not, please?

08:27.158 --> 08:28.856
- What, no time for cheer?

08:28.899 --> 08:31.293
We escaped the Library safe.

08:31.336 --> 08:33.687
You hid your friends.
They're safe, too.

08:33.730 --> 08:35.253
- Yeah, well, not Quentin.

08:35.297 --> 08:38.039
- And what exactly are you
gonna do about it, hmm?

08:38.082 --> 08:39.606
Besides scowl?

08:39.649 --> 08:41.216
- Save him.

08:41.259 --> 08:44.045
Warn him, I don't know.
I don't owe you an answer.

08:44.088 --> 08:45.046
- You wanna know what I think?

08:45.089 --> 08:46.874
- Jesus God, never.

08:46.917 --> 08:49.311
- I think we need to cast
another spell on that book

08:49.354 --> 08:50.791
for you.

08:50.834 --> 08:52.227
- I know exactly
where I need to go.

08:52.270 --> 08:53.750
Quentin's book showed me
where he is.

08:53.794 --> 08:55.273
And he only has
a couple days left.

08:55.317 --> 08:58.363
- Oh, so you trust one book
and not the other?

08:58.407 --> 09:01.366
That's funny.

09:01.410 --> 09:03.717
- There's only one place
I can try to make things right.

09:03.760 --> 09:05.240
- Redemption arc.

09:05.283 --> 09:08.199
Word of advice,
'cause I can see you need it.

09:08.243 --> 09:09.636
Apologize for
what you've done, fine.

09:09.679 --> 09:11.115
But never for who you are.

09:11.159 --> 09:12.247
'Cause you'll never
be able to change that.

09:12.290 --> 09:14.118
So why pretend?

09:18.775 --> 09:21.299
We're getting closer,
aren't we?

09:21.343 --> 09:24.825
- Just a few fountains away.

09:24.868 --> 09:27.436
- [sighs]
All I need

09:27.479 --> 09:29.307
is one moment

09:29.351 --> 09:31.832
to find my friends
and tell them I'm alive.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.964
Help me.

09:34.008 --> 09:35.966
Or I'm kicking you
out of the Happy Place.

09:36.010 --> 09:37.141
I can do that.

09:37.185 --> 09:39.622
Right?
- Yeah.

09:41.972 --> 09:44.235
There's a door somewhere.

09:44.279 --> 09:47.151
Hidden deep
in a forgotten remembrance.

09:47.195 --> 09:48.762
- Forgotten remembrance?

09:48.805 --> 09:50.764
- For me it was the door
to my childhood bedroom.

09:50.807 --> 09:53.244
But not...part of the memory.

09:53.288 --> 09:54.898
Just...

09:54.942 --> 09:56.465
just there.
- What memory?

09:56.508 --> 09:59.207
Where--how did
you get there, Charlton?

09:59.250 --> 10:01.731
- You can get to any memory.

10:01.775 --> 10:04.081
You just think on it
and walk outside.

10:04.125 --> 10:06.170
The one you seek, though,
is difficult to find.

10:06.214 --> 10:07.781
It's hidden well.

10:07.824 --> 10:09.783
Even from you.

10:09.826 --> 10:11.785
It hides in the place
you think of least

10:11.828 --> 10:14.657
because you don't wish to.

10:14.701 --> 10:15.745
Why?

10:15.789 --> 10:18.052
Because it's so terrible.

10:18.095 --> 10:19.967
- Huh.
So just my most

10:20.010 --> 10:22.317
repressed and traumatic memory.

10:22.360 --> 10:25.407
This'll be fun.

10:25.450 --> 10:27.931
Come on, Charlton.

10:27.975 --> 10:29.411
Time to take a walk
down memory lane.

10:29.454 --> 10:31.326
- Wait, wait, wait.

10:31.369 --> 10:33.110
Why do I have to come?
- You're coming.

10:33.154 --> 10:36.157
- Are you sure this is
the right one?

10:36.200 --> 10:37.767
- What, you don't
trust the book?

10:37.811 --> 10:39.160
- Well, no, it's just I--

10:39.203 --> 10:40.944
well, I've never seen one
locked before.

10:40.988 --> 10:43.381
- Here.

10:49.387 --> 10:52.390
[stones clicking]

10:56.394 --> 10:57.700
[grunts]

11:10.234 --> 11:12.236
I'll throw this down for you
in case you change your mind

11:12.280 --> 11:13.498
and you wanna climb back up.

11:13.542 --> 11:16.327
- Oh, very good.

11:19.548 --> 11:23.117
Right.

11:23.160 --> 11:26.468
Well, Alice, I suppose
this is good-bye.

11:26.511 --> 11:29.427
I do hope wherever you go is...

11:29.471 --> 11:31.560
is where you're supposed to be.

11:31.603 --> 11:33.257
- Same to you.

11:33.301 --> 11:37.000
- Right.
Well, here goes...

11:38.915 --> 11:41.744
[water splashes]

11:59.936 --> 12:03.766
- Hey, 23.
Can I get a ride?

12:03.810 --> 12:06.377
- I ain't your personal Uber.

12:06.421 --> 12:08.553
I'm back to Earth
after finishing the eggs,

12:08.597 --> 12:09.946
which I'm telling myself
come from a chicken.

12:09.990 --> 12:11.513
- It'll be real quick.

12:11.556 --> 12:13.428
I just need to get
my birthright box.

12:13.471 --> 12:14.777
And I'd love to do that

12:14.821 --> 12:15.865
before having to break
the Eliot news

12:15.909 --> 12:17.519
to the whole castle.

12:17.562 --> 12:19.521
Because that's not gonna be
a short convo.

12:19.564 --> 12:21.784
- Yeah, I'm helping Julia
with a god power thing.

12:21.828 --> 12:23.568
- You're seriously
blowing me off

12:23.612 --> 12:25.570
to score points
with your crush?

12:25.614 --> 12:27.442
- I'm the only one that
can perform the ritual.

12:27.485 --> 12:30.662
You're the one that brought
your fuckboy with you.

12:30.706 --> 12:32.403
- I brought Josh

12:32.447 --> 12:34.754
'cause we needed a decent cook.

12:34.797 --> 12:35.929
And we're cool.

12:35.972 --> 12:37.757
- Just like Julia
and me are cool.

12:37.800 --> 12:40.585
Cool?
- Cool, so about that ride?

12:40.629 --> 12:43.588
- Thanks for breakfast.

12:43.632 --> 12:46.504
- High King Margo, you're back!

12:47.941 --> 12:49.943
Where's Eliot?

12:55.862 --> 12:57.951
- Hey, Julia, uh...

12:57.994 --> 12:59.996
ready to run some diagnostics?

13:00.040 --> 13:03.870
Sup, Shoshana?
- Oh, we already ran them.

13:03.913 --> 13:05.436
- Oh, uh...

13:05.480 --> 13:06.437
Okay, what did they say?

13:06.481 --> 13:07.787
- Inconclusive.

13:07.830 --> 13:09.919
Uh, we're looking for
the right ritual to try.

13:09.963 --> 13:12.008
- But, um,
I'm her follower now,

13:12.052 --> 13:15.316
so I can handle it.

13:15.359 --> 13:18.449
- Right, so I'll just--
- Oh, do you happen to know

13:18.493 --> 13:20.060
any diagnostics to run

13:20.103 --> 13:23.498
on pseudo-gods or whatever?

13:23.541 --> 13:24.673
- Can't say that I do.

13:24.716 --> 13:27.458
- Mm.
Oh, so...

13:27.502 --> 13:31.027
We're good here, then.

13:31.071 --> 13:32.463
- Right.

13:32.507 --> 13:34.335
I'm gonna bounce.

13:34.378 --> 13:36.467
Uh, text me if you, uh,

13:36.511 --> 13:38.948
need a ride, or...

13:38.992 --> 13:40.080
something.

13:40.123 --> 13:41.081
- Thanks, Penny.

13:41.124 --> 13:43.039
- [gasps] Oh, shit, I--

13:43.083 --> 13:45.041
I totally forgot to ask

13:45.085 --> 13:46.826
if you have any
magical wards or cloaks.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.131
They could be interfering.

13:48.175 --> 13:50.699
- Uh, yeah, a massive
cloaking spell.

13:50.742 --> 13:52.962
This evil bitch
Irene McAllister is after me--

13:53.006 --> 13:54.877
so, uh, you can't remove it.
I need it.

13:54.921 --> 13:57.575
- Oh, crap, I just did.

13:57.619 --> 13:59.839
Um, just, um, give me
30 seconds.

13:59.882 --> 14:03.451
I'll protect you.

14:03.494 --> 14:04.887
- Julia.

