29:31.770 --> 29:32.814
Yeah.

29:43.607 --> 29:45.958
- That should do it.

29:46.001 --> 29:49.222
It just needs to drain and...

29:49.265 --> 29:51.528
for a minute or two.

29:51.572 --> 29:54.923
- You can, uh, leave now.

29:54.967 --> 29:58.144
Uh, when Julia gets out
of the Brakebills ward,

29:58.187 --> 30:01.060
she'll text me
and I'll meet her in the park.

30:01.103 --> 30:03.192
Then we trap the Monster today,
not in two days.

30:03.236 --> 30:04.672
So we're good.

30:04.715 --> 30:06.195
Deathly fate averted.

30:06.239 --> 30:07.762
- I should--I should
be there with you

30:07.806 --> 30:09.720
just in case what happens
in the book starts happening.

30:09.764 --> 30:10.721
- I'm about to kill my friend.

30:10.765 --> 30:12.288
It's a monster, I know,

30:12.332 --> 30:14.160
but it's a monster
with his face and eyes

30:14.203 --> 30:16.292
and I'm just--I don't

30:16.336 --> 30:18.512
have space for us right now.

30:18.555 --> 30:20.253
- I'm not asking you to!

30:24.474 --> 30:28.522
"A dog approached,
wanting to play.

30:28.565 --> 30:32.091
"The owner followed to talk
to Quentin, distracting him.

30:32.134 --> 30:33.440
"And in that moment,

30:33.483 --> 30:36.269
"The Monster saw
the stone's blood and Quentin,

30:36.312 --> 30:40.664
"and, with a mere thought,
sliced him apart,

30:40.708 --> 30:45.147
so ending the story
of Quentin Coldwater."

30:45.191 --> 30:46.975
I didn't come here
to make up with you.

30:47.019 --> 30:48.672
I came here to save your life.

30:48.716 --> 30:50.500
I'm just trying to figure out
how to fix

30:50.544 --> 30:53.416
this mountain of shit
that I've created.

30:53.460 --> 30:57.681
- Well, it's gonna take
a lot more than just my life.

31:02.512 --> 31:06.081
- I sent Christopher Plover
to the Poison World.

31:06.125 --> 31:08.257
I figure that should give me
some points in my favor.

31:08.301 --> 31:10.085
- You what?

31:10.129 --> 31:12.305
- Well, I was supposed to
send him to a peaceful world,

31:12.348 --> 31:13.306
but I thought that maybe
he would do something

31:13.349 --> 31:14.655
to a little kid and--

31:14.698 --> 31:16.396
and you know what,
he doesn't deserve peace.

31:16.439 --> 31:19.399
- Oh, my God. Oh.
[groans]

31:19.442 --> 31:21.836
Sorry, I'm back
where you were confessing

31:21.880 --> 31:23.794
to murdering my favorite
children's book author

31:23.838 --> 31:25.579
and yeah, I know, he's evil,

31:25.622 --> 31:28.190
but it's--
- But does that make me good?

31:28.234 --> 31:32.803
Does killing him make me
better or worse?

31:32.847 --> 31:34.805
- I don't know.

31:37.591 --> 31:39.723
- I am trying.

31:39.767 --> 31:44.163
Okay, Quentin?
I am always trying.

31:44.206 --> 31:47.731
So if you have some recipe
for perfect redemption,

31:47.775 --> 31:49.342
just tell me.

31:49.385 --> 31:51.126
Because I can't change
the way that you feel,

31:51.170 --> 31:53.041
so just...

31:58.133 --> 32:01.049
There's a spell...

32:01.093 --> 32:02.703
Okay, there's a spell in here

32:02.746 --> 32:04.531
that...

32:04.574 --> 32:07.055
that will tell me
where I'm supposed to go.

32:07.099 --> 32:08.230
So just let me come with you

32:08.274 --> 32:09.710
and then do this spell with me.

32:09.753 --> 32:11.886
And then wherever
it says to go, I'll go,

32:11.930 --> 32:13.322
and I will stay there
for good, okay?

32:13.366 --> 32:14.671
Just let me help you.

32:18.240 --> 32:19.807
- Wherever it says?

32:24.246 --> 32:27.728
Do you promise?

32:27.771 --> 32:30.774
- Promise.

32:32.602 --> 32:34.126
- Do whatever you gotta do.

32:34.169 --> 32:35.823
Just get it open.

32:38.434 --> 32:40.654
- This seems rash,
even for you.

32:40.697 --> 32:43.222
- Well, like my ex always said,

32:43.265 --> 32:45.267
I'll be happy once that box
is open.

32:45.311 --> 32:46.790
- Margo, have you cried yet?

32:46.834 --> 32:48.836
For Eliot?

32:48.879 --> 32:50.751
- Fen, I'm only gonna
say this once.

32:50.794 --> 32:55.582
Me joining your sad-face
therapy party is dumb.

32:55.625 --> 33:01.283
Because I can't cry out
all the sadness ever.

33:01.327 --> 33:03.459
Because if I start,

33:03.503 --> 33:07.724
I'll never stop, understand?

33:07.768 --> 33:11.598
I'll be useless forever.

33:11.641 --> 33:13.513
And somebody has to rule
this kingdom,

33:13.556 --> 33:15.167
and I will be God-damned

33:15.210 --> 33:16.603
if I drop the ball

33:16.646 --> 33:18.648
'cause I was too busy
lamenting with my tits out,

33:18.692 --> 33:21.608
all right?

33:21.651 --> 33:23.436
- Your Majesty.

33:23.479 --> 33:26.134
With deep regret
I must inform you,

33:26.178 --> 33:29.181
the royal sheep choir?
They've gone silent too.

33:29.224 --> 33:30.617
- But we need them
for the memorial.

33:30.660 --> 33:33.620
Who else will sing
the Bleats of Despair?

33:33.663 --> 33:36.144
- High King Margo.

33:45.675 --> 33:47.460
- A talking lizard
of the Dunes.

33:47.503 --> 33:49.462
I've only ever read
about these.

33:49.505 --> 33:54.162
- Well, what's my birthright,
you scaly shit?

33:58.775 --> 34:00.951
- It's the talking animals.

34:00.995 --> 34:03.476
They've all been struck dumb.

34:03.519 --> 34:06.174
- Well, shit.

34:06.218 --> 34:07.654
All right, Fen.

34:07.697 --> 34:09.699
I think I will do a ritual.
Earth specialty.

34:09.743 --> 34:11.440
The sleep of solitude.

34:11.484 --> 34:13.703
I pop an Ambien, everyone
leaves me alone till noon.

34:13.747 --> 34:16.228
That'll be perfect.

34:19.883 --> 34:22.799
- Mm, I never asked.

34:22.843 --> 34:25.585
When you found your door, um...

34:25.628 --> 34:29.197
what memory was it?

34:32.374 --> 34:34.246
- The day that I left home.

34:34.289 --> 34:35.899
- That's it?

34:35.943 --> 34:38.337
That's your most
traumatic memory?

34:38.380 --> 34:39.512
- Yes.

34:39.555 --> 34:41.731
Because I left...

34:41.775 --> 34:43.472
Home.

34:43.516 --> 34:45.213
- But it was
when you were confronted

34:45.257 --> 34:47.955
with what you fear most.

34:47.998 --> 34:49.826
- Great.

34:49.870 --> 34:53.221
So just figure out what that is

34:53.265 --> 34:55.441
and I'll make a distraction,

34:55.484 --> 34:57.791
and then--and then you can
go there.

34:57.834 --> 35:00.924
- I know you're
just a memory, but...

35:00.968 --> 35:04.363
you're a very generous one.

35:04.406 --> 35:08.802
- Well, you sacrifice
for people you love.

35:08.845 --> 35:11.718
- Oh, shit.

35:11.761 --> 35:14.460
I get it.

35:14.503 --> 35:19.943
Q, I'm gonna take you
up on that.

35:22.120 --> 35:24.774
Lead the creatures
to my puberty.

35:24.818 --> 35:26.385
Go bravely.

35:27.386 --> 35:29.475
- Okay.

35:34.654 --> 35:36.612
- I know where I need to go.

35:39.398 --> 35:41.313
- Did it happen?

35:41.356 --> 35:45.839
- Fifty years.

35:45.882 --> 35:47.754
- It happened.

35:51.975 --> 35:53.760
- Okay, so they should
be coming from there.

35:53.803 --> 35:55.283
I'll stand here.
He'll come to me.

35:55.327 --> 35:58.199
And then you drench him.

36:01.333 --> 36:02.856
- It was sort of beautiful.

36:02.899 --> 36:04.945
- It really was.

36:04.988 --> 36:07.861
- I know this sounds dumb...

36:07.904 --> 36:10.211
but us.
We--

36:10.255 --> 36:11.212
You know, think about it.

36:11.256 --> 36:15.173
Like, we--we work.

36:15.216 --> 36:17.218
And we know it 'cause
we've lived it.

36:17.262 --> 36:20.265
Who gets that kind
of proof of concept?

36:24.834 --> 36:26.401
- We were just injected with

36:26.445 --> 36:28.229
a half-century of emotion,

36:28.273 --> 36:31.928
so I get that maybe
you're not thinking clearly.

36:31.972 --> 36:33.887
- No, I'm just saying,
what if we...

36:33.930 --> 36:35.802
gave it a shot?

36:38.021 --> 36:40.807
I mean, would that
be that crazy?

36:43.288 --> 36:47.422
Why the fuck not?
I...

36:47.466 --> 36:50.860
- I know you and you...

36:50.904 --> 36:52.558
aren't...

36:52.601 --> 36:55.822
- What's the matter?
- Don't be naive. It matters.

36:55.865 --> 36:57.432
Q, come on.

36:57.476 --> 37:00.522
I love you, but...

37:00.566 --> 37:02.568
you have to know
that that's not me

37:02.611 --> 37:04.265
and that's definitely not you,

37:04.309 --> 37:07.573
not when...
not when we have a choice.

37:10.315 --> 37:11.838
- Okay. I...

37:11.881 --> 37:15.233
Okay.

37:15.276 --> 37:17.060
Sorry, I...

37:20.150 --> 37:23.502
- What the hell
is wrong with you?

37:23.545 --> 37:27.549
And what the hell
are you doing?

37:30.160 --> 37:33.381
- Q, the dog.

37:35.514 --> 37:37.080
- Hi.
- Sorry about him.

37:37.124 --> 37:38.212
Train 'em all you want,
they're still gonna do

37:38.256 --> 37:39.474
what they're gonna do,
you know?

37:39.518 --> 37:40.475
- Mm-hmm.

37:40.519 --> 37:42.172
- You have a dog?

37:42.216 --> 37:45.045
- Q, she's the distraction.
- Hmm? No, I...

37:45.088 --> 37:47.265
right, sorry, I got--uh.

37:47.308 --> 37:48.570
- All right, man.

37:50.137 --> 37:51.486
- Okay.

37:51.530 --> 37:52.922
Q, I'm gonna pour
the blood on him, okay?

37:52.966 --> 37:54.228
You just run right now, please.

37:54.272 --> 37:56.186
- No, look,
stick to the plan. Go.

37:56.230 --> 37:58.363
They're coming.

38:00.016 --> 38:02.192
- Someone good and true

38:02.236 --> 38:03.324
loves you.

38:03.368 --> 38:05.108
And he went out on a limb.

38:05.152 --> 38:06.980
And, yeah,
it was a little crazy,

38:07.023 --> 38:08.460
but you knew.

38:08.503 --> 38:11.201
You knew this was a moment
that truly mattered

38:11.245 --> 38:12.638
and you just snuffed it out.

38:12.681 --> 38:15.641
[tense music]

38:15.684 --> 38:22.909
â™ª

38:23.649 --> 38:25.564
Q, I'm sorry.

38:30.003 --> 38:31.483
I was afraid.

38:31.526 --> 38:34.921
And when I'm afraid,
I run away.

38:55.463 --> 38:57.378
If I ever get out of here, Q,

38:57.422 --> 38:58.553
know that when I'm braver

38:58.597 --> 39:01.556
it's 'cause I learned it
from you.

39:07.606 --> 39:09.129
- Quentin.

39:09.172 --> 39:11.697
â™ª

39:11.740 --> 39:14.743
[door opens]

39:14.787 --> 39:21.968
â™ª

39:31.499 --> 39:36.243
- Q.

39:36.286 --> 39:37.723
Q.

39:37.766 --> 39:40.421
[laughing]

39:40.465 --> 39:41.640
It's me.

39:41.683 --> 39:44.294
It's Eliot.

39:44.338 --> 39:45.687
- Okay, no games, come on.

39:45.731 --> 39:47.602
Let's just go.
- It's Eliot.

39:47.646 --> 39:49.517
- No, bullshit.
Come on.

39:49.561 --> 39:51.432
- Fifty years.

39:51.476 --> 39:54.043
Who gets proof of concept
like that?

39:54.087 --> 39:55.349
- What?

39:55.393 --> 39:58.657
- Peaches and plums,
motherfucker.

39:58.700 --> 40:01.442
I'm alive in here.

40:01.486 --> 40:04.314
- Eliot.

40:04.358 --> 40:06.316
Whoa, no!

40:19.286 --> 40:22.071
- Did it work?

40:22.115 --> 40:24.683
- I hope so.

40:27.555 --> 40:30.819
- You fucked it up.
I warned you.

40:30.863 --> 40:33.518
- No!
- Wait, don't!

40:35.215 --> 40:37.173
- Look what you did.

40:37.217 --> 40:39.262
- Iris.

40:39.306 --> 40:43.266
Fancy seeing you here.

40:43.310 --> 40:46.095
I'd like it back now.

40:46.139 --> 40:49.142
- [gasps]

40:53.189 --> 40:55.061
- I'm sorry.

40:57.890 --> 40:59.500
- You tried to trick me.

40:59.544 --> 41:01.415
- No. No, it wasn't--

41:01.459 --> 41:04.200
- The plan worked, right, Q?

41:04.244 --> 41:05.637
- Who is this now?

41:05.680 --> 41:07.726
- Right the plan, the--we--

41:07.769 --> 41:09.379
we got Iris for you.

41:09.423 --> 41:11.512
We couldn't tell you
because she was watching,

41:11.556 --> 41:13.209
but we...

41:13.253 --> 41:16.343
we did it.

41:16.386 --> 41:20.565
- This was all
just a plan...for me?

41:20.608 --> 41:22.262
- Yeah.

41:22.305 --> 41:24.699
- Yeah, yeah, and, um...

41:24.743 --> 41:26.658
and here's the best part.

41:26.701 --> 41:28.137
We didn't wanna show you

41:28.181 --> 41:29.835
till you had the piece
from Iris.

41:29.878 --> 41:31.706
According to this,

41:31.750 --> 41:34.579
uh, all those organs?

41:34.622 --> 41:36.668
They're building blocks.

41:36.711 --> 41:39.671
Trying to piece together
a body.

41:39.714 --> 41:42.325
Is it yours?

41:47.200 --> 41:50.246
- Impressive.

41:50.290 --> 41:53.423
- Eliot's alive.

41:53.467 --> 41:54.773
- What?

41:54.816 --> 41:58.298
- He's alive.

42:04.652 --> 42:07.350
- Any minute now.

42:16.621 --> 42:18.623
I was just about to leave, I...

42:22.322 --> 42:23.932
Does she know that
I just saved your life?

42:23.976 --> 42:25.238
- No.

42:25.281 --> 42:27.675
I never thanked you for that.

42:27.719 --> 42:29.808
He made me hesitate,
and if I hadn't...

42:29.851 --> 42:33.463
Eliot would be gone.

42:33.507 --> 42:34.769
If the Monster's
building a body,

42:34.813 --> 42:36.945
maybe there's a way
that we can...

42:36.989 --> 42:38.251
save him.

42:38.294 --> 42:40.470
- I can help.

42:40.514 --> 42:44.300
Just let me stay.

42:44.344 --> 42:45.432
- You saved my life.

42:45.475 --> 42:47.434
You can save my life 50 times.

42:47.477 --> 42:49.610
It's not gonna change...

42:49.654 --> 42:52.265
anything between us.

42:52.308 --> 42:54.789
I loved you.

43:01.361 --> 43:05.191
Maybe you couldn't trust that.

43:09.848 --> 43:12.764
It's done.

43:24.558 --> 43:26.952
Good-bye, Alice.
